-- Polish Stocks: KGHM Polska Miedz, Bank Pekao, PKO Are Active
-- B y   P i o t r   B u j n i c k i
-- 2012-06-06T16:10:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/polish-stocks-kghm-polska-miedz-new-world-resources-are-active.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  advanced 3.5
percent, the biggest daily gain in six months, to 2,110.91, at
the 5:30 p.m. in Warsaw.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  KGHM Polska Miedz SA (KGH)  , the copper producer with the
biggest European mine output, climbed 3.5 percent to 130.4
zloty, the most in two months as the metal rallied.  Bank Pekao SA (PEO)  : Poland’s second-biggest lender
posted the biggest single-day gain since Nov. 30 and  PKO Bank
Polski SA (PKO)  , the country’s largest lender, gained the
most since Dec. 5 as stocks rose worldwide on speculation
European policy makers will act to spur economic growth. Bank
Pekao shares rose 6.8 percent to 139 zloty and PKO Bank Polski
climbed 4.8 percent to 32.70 zloty.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Piotr Bujnicki in Warsaw 
